{"TopicId":189934,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"\u0026quot;Spaceshuttle\u0026quot; starts spinning violently after booster separation","CreatedByName":"UncleManuel","CreatedById":201419,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-21T21:50:53Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"UncleManuel","CreatedById":201419,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-21T21:50:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI legoed together a Spaceshuttle clone and noticed some unwanted behavior.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002220191121221506_1.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022http://manuel-aka-mdk.net/pics/KSP/20191121221506_1.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter booster separation at around 20000 meters the whole vehicle starts to oscillate then roll violently and uncontrollably. No matter what I do the centrifugal forces will ultimately rip the external tank off...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:blink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_blink.png\u0022 title=\u0022:blink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSooooo, the big question is: why does it behave like that?\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ph34r.png\u0022 title=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002220191121220558_1.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022http://manuel-aka-mdk.net/pics/KSP/20191121220558_1.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ph0x","CreatedById":201495,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-22T08:58:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t see an engine on it...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fierce Wolf","CreatedById":200019,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-22T12:38:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore struts? Sepratrons to push away the boosters?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-22T12:50:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOff center thrust. \u00A0The thrust centerline is above the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, so that starts the spinning. \u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nkeep in mind that the shuttle does not fly straight ahesd.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe following is a good explanation by Scott Manley of the changes in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E of the space shuttle and the different thrust vectoring available in the engines involved\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nk\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/otv7lJmLJtQ?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"drpunk","CreatedById":200335,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-22T12:51:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d hazard a guess at centre of mass and centre of thrust.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBoth change drastically without the boosters\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-11-22T12:52:00Z\u0022 title=\u002211/22/2019 12:52  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 22, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by drpunk\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UncleManuel","CreatedById":201419,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-23T18:42:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe weird thing is that it spins on the \u003Cstrong\u003Eroll axis\u003C/strong\u003E, not the pitch axis...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:blink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_blink.png\u0022 title=\u0022:blink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTakeoff can be a bit wobbly on inclination change but the uncontrollable spinning occurs \u003Cstrong\u003Eafter \u003C/strong\u003Ebooster separation.\u00A0\u00A0I really don\u0027t understand why it\u0027s rolling around the vertical axis like that...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-23T18:47:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223708934\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022189934\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221574534531\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201419\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022UncleManuel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, UncleManuel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe weird thing is that it spins on the \u003Cstrong\u003Eroll axis\u003C/strong\u003E, not the pitch axis...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:blink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_blink.png\u0022 title=\u0022:blink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTakeoff can be a bit wobbly on inclination change but the uncontrollable spinning occurs \u003Cstrong\u003Eafter \u003C/strong\u003Ebooster separation.\u00A0\u00A0I really don\u0027t understand why it\u0027s rolling around the vertical axis like that...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVideo would help. \u00A0Also, the craft file\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CBase","CreatedById":189476,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-25T08:03:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn your screenshot \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E is not enabled, although you have \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters at the nose. Without \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E engine gimbal will counter any derivation from course as control surfaces get less effective at altitude.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBe aware that roll and yaw are connected if controls are off axis with center of mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}